head: Divorce Notice.
ab: TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON, COUNTY OF THURSTON.
p: In the United States District Court of the Second Judicial District, of W. T., holding terms at Olympia. November Term, 1866.
ab: Herbert Jeal, vs Petition for Divorce. Mary Ann Jeal.
p: YOU ARE HEREBY NOTIFIED that Herbert Jeal, Plaintiff herein, has filed his complaint against you in said Court, which will come on to be heard at the next term thereof, which shall commence two months or more after the 28th day of July, 1866, and unless you appear at said term and answer the same will be taken as confessed, and the prayer thereof granted.
The object and prayer of said complaint is to dissolve the bonds of matrimony now existing between you and plaintiff.
ANDREW J. MOSES, Attorney for Defendant.
Dated Olympia, July 28th, 1866. Complaint filed July 28th, 1866.
